1
00:00:04,713 --> 00:00:05,631
[Growls]

2
00:00:05,756 --> 00:00:06,882
[Dolphins chatter]

3
00:00:10,511 --> 00:00:11,678
[Screeches]

4
00:00:13,430 --> 00:00:14,515
J Adventure time J

5
00:00:14,556 --> 00:00:15,807
J Come on, grab your friends &

6
00:00:15,891 --> 00:00:18,602
> We'll go
to very distant lands 7

7
00:00:18,644 --> 00:00:20,896
J With Finn and Jake
and Susan Strong J

8
00:00:21,021 --> 00:00:22,648
J And possibly BMO 7

9
00:00:22,648 --> 00:00:24,483
J It's adventure time 7

10
00:00:32,824 --> 00:00:34,201
FINN:
I'm leaving the island.

11
00:00:34,201 --> 00:00:36,078
I'm leaving my mom.

12
00:00:36,828 --> 00:00:39,581
What a wild adventure,
yellow stretching dog.

13
00:00:39,581 --> 00:00:41,667
You said it, beautiful baby boy.

14
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:43,210
-[Rumbling]
- BOTH: Huh?

15
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:47,714
The Guardian!

16
00:00:47,798 --> 00:00:48,840
Oh, no!

17
00:00:48,924 --> 00:00:50,842
We never should've left
the island!

18
00:00:50,968 --> 00:00:52,928
Now we die!

19
00:00:56,974 --> 00:00:58,809
MINERVA:
See? You die.

20
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:04,064
By my calculations,
you stand a 0.00001% chance

21
00:01:04,147 --> 00:01:05,691
of making it past the Guardian.

22
00:01:05,774 --> 00:01:07,067
Can't you just turn him off?

23
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:09,069
He's here for our protection.

24
00:01:09,069 --> 00:01:11,196
If we were tough enough
to make it past him,

25
00:01:11,196 --> 00:01:12,906
we wouldn't need him!

26
00:01:12,948 --> 00:01:13,699
But...

27
00:01:13,782 --> 00:01:14,950
But none of that matters,

28
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:17,661
because you can stay safe
right here with me!

29
00:01:17,661 --> 00:01:19,830
Minerva-bot,
hug my son again.

30
00:01:20,455 --> 00:01:23,709
Mom, listen, I'm so happy
I finally got to meet you

31
00:01:23,792 --> 00:01:25,335
and learn about humans.

32
00:01:25,335 --> 00:01:27,588
But I have to get back
to my life eventually.

33
00:01:27,671 --> 00:01:30,340
Did you see the simulation?
You'd die!

34
00:01:30,465 --> 00:01:31,466
Let's watch it again.

35
00:01:31,466 --> 00:01:33,302
[Tape rewinding]

36
00:01:35,095 --> 00:01:36,930
[indistinct conversations,
laughter]

37
00:01:36,972 --> 00:01:38,056
[Bells jingle]

38
00:01:38,974 --> 00:01:40,225
Be right with you.

39
00:01:40,309 --> 00:01:42,311
Excuse me.
Where's the soup?

40
00:01:42,352 --> 00:01:43,228
Ugh.

41
00:01:43,312 --> 00:01:45,814
I told you yesterday.
We are a toy store.

42
00:01:45,856 --> 00:01:47,983
We don't sell sou--
Wooh?

43
00:01:49,735 --> 00:01:51,361
Hi, Frieda.

44
00:01:51,486 --> 00:01:53,739
Kara.
What are you doing here?

45
00:01:53,822 --> 00:01:56,491
Hope you didn't come
to get the soup!

46
00:01:57,993 --> 00:02:01,455
I, um -- I wanted to apologize
for everything.

47
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:03,999
You knew there was more to life
than just the islands,

48
00:02:03,999 --> 00:02:06,126
and I -- I didn't believe you.

49
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:08,629
I know you can't
ever forgive me,

50
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:11,006
but I am truly sorry.

51
00:02:11,673 --> 00:02:13,008
Don't sweat it.

52
00:02:13,050 --> 00:02:15,052
Awkward feelings averted.

53
00:02:15,052 --> 00:02:16,637
Let's have some soup!

54
00:02:16,678 --> 00:02:19,389
And who's this little
electronic cutie?

55
00:02:19,431 --> 00:02:21,141
What happened to you?

56
00:02:21,183 --> 00:02:25,687
I grew up, and I learned
to accept the Founders' truth.

57
00:02:25,687 --> 00:02:27,564
Frieda.

58
00:02:29,191 --> 00:02:31,068
The outside world's really cool.

59
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:32,319
I have cool friends.

60
00:02:32,402 --> 00:02:33,654
Yeah!

61
00:02:33,695 --> 00:02:34,905
I live in a cool treehouse.

62
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:35,906
Yeah!

63
00:02:35,947 --> 00:02:37,699
- I go on cool quests.
- Yeah!

64
00:02:37,699 --> 00:02:40,410
- That sounds dangerous!
- JAKE: No!

65
00:02:40,452 --> 00:02:43,080
But people need danger
in order to grow.

66
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:45,332
How will you all survive
when you leave the island?

67
00:02:45,415 --> 00:02:48,210
Leaving the island
would destroy us.

68
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:50,087
Besides,
why would they want to leave?

69
00:02:50,212 --> 00:02:52,339
We have everything
you could need.

70
00:02:52,339 --> 00:02:53,173
You hungry?

71
00:02:53,215 --> 00:02:54,424
[Shaps fingers]
Always.

72
00:02:54,466 --> 00:02:57,344
Minerva-bot, please show him
today's specials.

73
00:03:01,098 --> 00:03:03,433
MINERVA-BOT: Happy home burgers
with choco fries

74
00:03:03,475 --> 00:03:05,977
and our famous
cozy banana split blankie.

75
00:03:06,103 --> 00:03:08,730
Gimme all them specials
in one bowl.

76
00:03:11,608 --> 00:03:13,694
[Munching loudly]

77
00:03:13,735 --> 00:03:14,695
Jake!

78
00:03:14,736 --> 00:03:15,987
I'm so glad you like it.

79
00:03:16,071 --> 00:03:17,364
[Munching continues]

80
00:03:17,364 --> 00:03:19,199
If you're not gonna hear
what I'm saying,

81
00:03:19,241 --> 00:03:20,450
then look inside my head!

82
00:03:20,492 --> 00:03:21,868
Danger zone!

83
00:03:21,868 --> 00:03:23,120
[Zap]

84
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:36,007
Finn!

85
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:38,009
I'm okay.

86
00:03:38,093 --> 00:03:39,886
Sweet remembrances, bro.

87
00:03:39,970 --> 00:03:42,347
Your world seems so chaotic.

88
00:03:42,389 --> 00:03:45,225
Your ruler's a piece of gum.
Your friend’'s a vampire.

89
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:46,393
You dated a bit of fire.

90
00:03:46,518 --> 00:03:48,895
Your life
is constantly in danger!

91
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:51,398
It's my home.
It's where I belong.

92
00:03:51,398 --> 00:03:54,735
As your mother, I think
you belong somewhere safe.

93
00:03:54,776 --> 00:03:57,612
It's not your responsibility
to fight monsters all the time.

94
00:03:57,654 --> 00:04:01,283
Let the grass kid do it
or the vampire girl.

95
00:04:02,159 --> 00:04:04,911
Minerva-bot 5,
ready the cloud chamber.

96
00:04:07,289 --> 00:04:09,416
Now, be a good boy
and get into this machine

97
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:11,543
so it can juice up
your precious essence.

98
00:04:11,626 --> 00:04:12,419
[Gasps]

99
00:04:12,419 --> 00:04:14,045
Pftttt!

100
00:04:14,171 --> 00:04:15,297
[Munching]

101
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:16,840
[Sighs]

102
00:04:16,882 --> 00:04:19,259
Mom, not only
am I not getting juiced,

103
00:04:19,342 --> 00:04:22,512
I'm gonna leave this place
and take everyone to freedom!

104
00:04:22,596 --> 00:04:24,598
Okay, sweetie,
but I think you'll find

105
00:04:24,639 --> 00:04:26,516
everyone's pretty happy here.

106
00:04:26,516 --> 00:04:30,353
FRIEDA: It's true.
I'm really, really happy here.

107
00:04:30,395 --> 00:04:33,231
Don't you remember
your dreams of exploration?

108
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:38,653
If I remember,
I might get...angry.

109
00:04:38,779 --> 00:04:41,907
You should be angry -- at me.

110
00:04:42,991 --> 00:04:45,118
Nah. I'm over it.

111
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:48,288
-[Indistinct conversations]
- FINN: Hey, everyone!

112
00:04:48,371 --> 00:04:50,290
Uh, excuse me.

113
00:04:51,166 --> 00:04:52,417
[High-pitched scream]

114
00:04:52,501 --> 00:04:53,543
[Conversations stop]

115
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:56,004
I know y'all like
living on this tiny island

116
00:04:56,046 --> 00:04:57,506
'cause it's safe and chill,

117
00:04:57,547 --> 00:04:59,299
but you don't have to live
like this.

118
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:02,177
- All right, thank you.
-[Crowd murmuring]

119
00:05:02,177 --> 00:05:03,303
Wait!

120
00:05:03,428 --> 00:05:05,180
You think
the outside world is scary?

121
00:05:05,263 --> 00:05:07,057
Well, you know
what's really scary?

122
00:05:07,057 --> 00:05:08,141
Bees!

123
00:05:08,183 --> 00:05:09,309
- Germs!
- Frogs!

124
00:05:09,392 --> 00:05:11,686
Crowds!
Ngyuhhh!

125
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:13,021
(\\[o

126
00:05:13,063 --> 00:05:15,690
Letting fear make
all your decisions for you.

127
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:17,943
[Crowd murmuring]

128
00:05:17,943 --> 00:05:20,695
You! Do you know
you have free will?

129
00:05:20,821 --> 00:05:22,906
Is -- Is that
what you're selling?

130
00:05:24,199 --> 00:05:27,160
You got to --
How do you even -- Ugh!

131
00:05:27,202 --> 00:05:28,829
FINN: How do you even know
if you're happy

132
00:05:28,912 --> 00:05:30,831
if someone else decided for you?

133
00:05:30,831 --> 00:05:32,332
Follow me!

134
00:05:32,457 --> 00:05:34,668
Don't you want to be able
to choose what you do?

135
00:05:34,709 --> 00:05:35,961
And where you go?

136
00:05:36,086 --> 00:05:37,838
CROWD:
Sounds hard.

137
00:05:37,838 --> 00:05:39,923
Yeah, but it's also fun.

138
00:05:39,965 --> 00:05:41,967
And boring.
And good and bad.

139
00:05:42,092 --> 00:05:43,677
Life's never just one thing.

140
00:05:43,718 --> 00:05:44,553
Yeah.

141
00:05:44,594 --> 00:05:46,847
We got freedom
smushed up inside our guts.

142
00:05:46,930 --> 00:05:49,474
We want to explore
and have experiences

143
00:05:49,474 --> 00:05:50,976
and learn new things.

144
00:05:51,101 --> 00:05:54,104
Kingdoms made of candy,
beautiful dragons,

145
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:57,440
fire-breathing princesses,
incredibly sad wizards.

146
00:05:57,482 --> 00:05:59,484
It's all waiting for you
across the ocean.

147
00:05:59,568 --> 00:06:01,695
So misguided.

148
00:06:01,736 --> 00:06:03,613
Hey, This guy is great!

149
00:06:03,697 --> 00:06:06,116
What are we
hanging around here for?

150
00:06:06,116 --> 00:06:07,617
-[Crowd murmuring]
- What?!

151
00:06:07,701 --> 00:06:10,328
I did want to leave the island
when I was younger, but --

152
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:12,706
You can leave now.
Just come with me.

153
00:06:12,747 --> 00:06:13,748
[Crowd cheering]

154
00:06:13,874 --> 00:06:15,250
They're actually
listening to him.

155
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:17,210
All aboard!

156
00:06:17,252 --> 00:06:19,504
[Cheering continues]

157
00:06:19,629 --> 00:06:21,590
Patch me in
to all Minerva-bots.

158
00:06:21,631 --> 00:06:23,508
Attention!

159
00:06:23,592 --> 00:06:26,887
For your protection, the entire
population of the islands

160
00:06:26,970 --> 00:06:28,388
will now be uploaded.

161
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:38,523
Once the field
has reached peak saturation,

162
00:06:38,607 --> 00:06:42,027
the brain maps of every citizen
will be simultaneously captured

163
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:45,030
and preserved in
the island chain brain frame.

164
00:06:45,113 --> 00:06:47,616
Say goodbye
to your meat bodies!

165
00:06:47,657 --> 00:06:48,909
[Crowd whimpering]

166
00:06:50,035 --> 00:06:50,911
Mom!

167
00:06:50,911 --> 00:06:52,621
[Whimpering continues]

168
00:06:57,042 --> 00:06:58,293
Stop!

169
00:06:59,002 --> 00:07:01,546
Hey! There's my boy!

170
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:03,632
Your cloud is
freaking us all out!

171
00:07:03,673 --> 00:07:06,051
Sweetie, you forced my hand.

172
00:07:06,134 --> 00:07:08,887
This is the only way
I can protect you.

173
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:13,433
You're only doing this
because I said I wouldn't stay.

174
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:14,768
So I'll stay.

175
00:07:14,809 --> 00:07:17,020
Just promise
to stop messing with people.

176
00:07:17,062 --> 00:07:18,897
I'm helping people.

177
00:07:18,939 --> 00:07:21,316
I know about helping people.

178
00:07:22,692 --> 00:07:23,568
[Zap]

179
00:07:36,665 --> 00:07:40,168
Finn, you -- you grew up
to be a helper, too?

180
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:44,547
If your world taught you
to behave like that,

181
00:07:44,589 --> 00:07:46,549
maybe it's not all bad.

182
00:07:47,092 --> 00:07:48,468
[All screaming]

183
00:07:52,097 --> 00:07:54,099
Vroom! Vroom!
[Imitates tires screeching]

184
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:56,851
Perhaps I acted rashly.

185
00:07:56,935 --> 00:07:59,562
I just didn't want
to lose you again.

186
00:07:59,604 --> 00:08:02,732
But I'll do everything I can
to help you leave this island.

187
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:06,611
I don't have to leave...
right away.

188
00:08:06,736 --> 00:08:09,364
I mean...you're my mom.

189
00:08:13,118 --> 00:08:15,120
[Crowd murmuring]

190
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:16,997
Ahoy!

191
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:19,457
Now boarding the historic voyage
of the humans

192
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:21,626
back to the land of Ooo!

193
00:08:22,627 --> 00:08:24,254
Oh, you mean right now?

194
00:08:24,254 --> 00:08:26,381
I thought you meant, like,
in a while.

195
00:08:26,381 --> 00:08:29,134
I've still got some things
to finish up.

196
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:31,011
We should definitely
keep in touch, though.

197
00:08:31,094 --> 00:08:34,431
[Crowd murmuring]

198
00:08:34,556 --> 00:08:37,434
You can't teach a fish to dance
overnight, son.

199
00:08:37,434 --> 00:08:40,186
Well, as long as
they got the option.

200
00:08:40,311 --> 00:08:42,564
Ready, Frieda?
Ready.

201
00:08:43,314 --> 00:08:44,816
[Boat horn blows]

202
00:08:44,899 --> 00:08:46,901
FINN:
I'm leaving the island.

203
00:08:46,943 --> 00:08:48,820
I'm leaving my mom.

204
00:08:49,571 --> 00:08:52,323
What a wild adventure,
yellow stretching dog.

205
00:08:52,407 --> 00:08:54,534
You said it, beautiful baby boy.

206
00:08:54,576 --> 00:08:56,327
-[Rumbling]
- BOTH: Huh?

207
00:09:00,582 --> 00:09:01,583
JAKE:
Oh, yeah.

208
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:09,466
FRIEDA: Psych!

209
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:12,469
Ha ha! That's right!

210
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:14,846
You got fooled by Frieda!

211
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:26,983
Hey, buddy.

212
00:09:27,859 --> 00:09:28,818
Aaah!

213
00:09:30,862 --> 00:09:32,363
\CEEEEE

214
00:09:32,447 --> 00:09:33,239
Aaaaaah...

215
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:34,449
...aaaaaah!

216
00:09:34,491 --> 00:09:36,076
...aaaaaah!

217
00:09:36,117 --> 00:09:37,077
Huh?

218
00:09:38,620 --> 00:09:39,996
Patching her in now.

219
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:44,584
Guardian, you have done
just a terrific job,

220
00:09:44,626 --> 00:09:46,753
but it's time to stand down.

221
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:56,262
[Boat horn blows]

222
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:58,973
When do I fire the torpedoes?

223
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:01,768
Kara, you ready to go?

224
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:05,647
Actually, I think we're headed
in a different direction.

225
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:07,649
Time for new memories.

226
00:10:12,487 --> 00:10:15,281
So, where are we going, Kara?

227
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:16,658
I've been thinking.

228
00:10:16,783 --> 00:10:19,160
I kind of like "Susan" better.

229
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:20,787
Okay, Susan.

230
00:10:29,671 --> 00:10:32,632
- Hmm. Homey.
- MINERVA: It was.

231
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:36,803
Take care of yourself in Ooo.

232
00:10:36,928 --> 00:10:38,680
Be careful
when you're eating blueberries.

233
00:10:38,763 --> 00:10:40,682
Too many can hurt your tummy.

234
00:10:43,268 --> 00:10:45,061
Your ship is moving
out of range.

235
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:47,063
Is this...really you?

236
00:10:47,147 --> 00:10:49,399
Once you uploaded your brain
and stuff, like,

237
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:51,401
are you still the same person?

238
00:10:51,442 --> 00:10:54,571
I don't know for sure,
but I feel like it's me.

239
00:10:54,571 --> 00:10:56,281
I hope that's enough.

240
00:10:59,534 --> 00:11:00,702
Goodbye.

241
00:11:18,469 --> 00:11:20,471
This party is so crazy!

